{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"A\n    \n      tauri-plugin-updater + GitHub Releases Recommended\n      The official Tauri 2 updater plugin. You publish a latest.json manifest to GitHub Releases (or a static URL). The plugin checks it, compares versions, downloads + verifies using Ed25519 signing, and installs. All update transport logic is handled by Tauri.\n      \n        \n          Pros\n          \n            Minimal code — plugin handles download, verify, install\n            Ed25519 signing built-in (separate from Apple notarization)\n            GitHub Actions can auto-generate the manifest on release\n            Works on macOS, Windows, Linux\n          \n        \n        \n          Cons\n          \n            Requires generating + storing an Ed25519 keypair as a GitHub secret\n            macOS Gatekeeper warnings without Apple notarization (expected for now)\n            No staged rollouts or A/B without extra tooling","choice":"a","id":null,"timestamp":1774736050648}
